lation and in the original, as I have done every year since 1968. This book is a literary study of the Iliad. I have not discussed historical, archaeologoical, or even linguistic questions except where they are directly relevant to literary interpretation. Throughout I have emphasized what is thematically, ethically, and artistically distinctive in the Iliad in contrast to the conventions of the poetic tradition of which it is an end product.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEpic poetry, GreekxHistory and criticism. 0aHeroes in literature. 0aTrojan WarxLiterature and the war. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aancient greece.  aancient greek lit.  aart and literature.  aclassical scholars.  acontemporary theorists.  acritical introduction.  aenglish majors.  aepic poem.  aethics and religion.  afamous literature.  agreek mythology.  agreek scholars.  ahomer.  ahomeric specialists.  ailiad themes.  ailiad.  alit scholars.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary criticism.  aliterary critics.  aliterary heroes.  aliterary interpretation.  aliterary studies.  aliterature students.  amodern criticism.  anonfiction.  apoetic tradition.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052005626840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520341067?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520341067423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520341067/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY